# Mandatory assignment 2

**XP-project in collaboration with Software Construction**



**Hand out:**         Week 40, 2018.

**Hand in:**         Week 43, Tuesday 23. October, no later than 16:00 (uploaded to Fronter)

**Hand in:**

The hand in consist of three parts:

1.  A written part handed in on Tuesday 23. October, consisting of:

A project report that documents the prototype and your system development. The requirement for the project report is:

1.
  - An iteration plan, consisting of three iterations.
  - The requirement for the system are documented for each iteration, using the prioritized&quot; user stories&quot; and estimates, and by reflecting on these.
  - The system design is to be documented in source code and the associated **test cases** , after the last iteration.
  - Documentation of the groups chosen code standard.
  - A guide for the acceptance test of each user story.

1. You must build an application prototype with the following minimum requirements.

- A Client / Server solution.
- A GUI via Spring or a corresponding alternative.
- A normalized database

1.  An oral presentation for the class is on Friday 26. October.

**A hand in, after the deadline, is considered to be a no hand in!!!!!!!!!**

**Oral presentation:**

The oral presentation for the class is on Friday 26. October. Each group will have 45 min to present, make sure that all group members participates.

The group must present essential details about:

- The Product – including a demonstration of the prototype.
- The Process – evaluate the individual XP-principles, group size, attendance, commitment productivity etc.
- Your professional competences, before and after the project.



**Approval:**

Participation in this project in the school is mandatory. The assignment is to be done in groups of approx. 8-10 students, and the groups are made by Cay.

The assignment is approved, if each group member presents part of the work results, and is able to answer clarifying questions in a satisfying manor that shows, that the student have participated in the group work.

**The assignment**

Each group gets a case about a fictitious company that needs an IT-system developed.

How to know what to build for the customer?

- Be prepared for your meetings with your customer, know what information you need from him.
- Make paper prototypes to uncover requirements
- Write down every decision made with your customer
- Write user stories with your customer, get them prioritized by your customer

**The product of each iteration must be tested/approved by the customer before continuing!**

All members of the group must attend the development at each school day. The group is self-governing and divides the roles of developer, project manager and/or scrum master between the members.

**You will have stand-up meeting every morning for 15 min. where you answers the tree scrum-meeting questions!**

**You have to use a SCRUM-board to control your development, on the wall or as an online tool!**

**Each student is to register used time for each user story** (5 minutes accuracy).

It is the project manager&#39;s job to keep track of the used time (both estimated and actually spend time) for all the students. **Make burndown charts after each iteration!**

_Totalization is done for each iteration:_

- Of the combined time consumption for each user story:

Example:

| User story | Estimatet time consumption | Actual time consumption |
| ---------- | -------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| xx | 2 | 2,5 |

_Hint:_ Start with a Project planning meeting where you divide roles, assignments etc. Remember to document plans, estimations and recorded consumption. Make sure that each student is aware of their responsibility.

**Important:**

According to XP, you do not work individually with assignments but in the project group – **so there is**  **mandatory attendance**  **in class during the project period!!!** It is, of course, allowed and expected, that you work on the project, outside normal classes.

# AdventureXP

The owner of the action center Adventure Alley needs a new IT-system to manage reservations of the activities, the equipment etc.









The following is known about AdventureXP:

- The center offers Activities such as Gocart, Minigolf, paintball, sumo wrestling etc.
- There are different age limits for the individual activities
- Private individuals can make reservations for the activities
- AdventureXP also offers company arrangements involving several activities

The center has the following employees:

- 2 employees for managing reservations
- 8 employees who manages the individual activities and the maintenance of equipment

At the moment, all reservations are made by telephone.
